<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=555040">Sage Asiago</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oxoxoxoxox>Oxoxo Xoxox</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1066<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/03 12:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mana burn</span><hr size=1> The nerf is fucking retarted seeing as how you can crit for 6500s using SoS or 7k+ with SoM <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68788" target="top">Oxoxo Xoxox ~ Arcanist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235386" target="top">Yumkin Stumpyshorts ~ Vicar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.queensidecastle.com/eq/twins2.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yugy>yugy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/03 1:03 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mana burn</span><hr size=1> The cap is 9492.  Why that is the cap, I have no idea.  It was 9492 before the recent patch to give us larger mana pools and it remains 9492.<br>
<br>
As to the aggro being nerfed, I have never gotten aggro from a MB, but then I don't MB while soloing.<br>
<br>
There was a time when you could &quot;under-crit&quot; and get about 3k from MB when 6k+ was your theoretical minimum.  That does seem to have been fixed in the last month or three.<br>
<br>
Crits now seem to have no effect other than telling others how much you hit for.  Its been at least 6 months since I had a MB go for more than 9492, with or w/o a crit. <p>Sage Yugy of the Nexus<BR>
Arcanist and Officer of Triune, Morell-Thule<BR>
<img src="http://www.asero.com/eq/yugy.jpg"><BR><br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310232"> Magelo </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=veladorn>Veladorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>I have needs too!</span><br>  Posts: 1323<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/03 9:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> same</span><hr size=1> I don't recomment Manaburn for most wizards.  In my case I find that sometimes when I'm getting mad manaregen with bardsong and c5 sitting on a horse, etc, when certain mobs gets under 10% health Im still at 80+ mana.  In those cases, I go ahead and manaburn and often hit for 9492.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=malakriss>Malakriss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 292<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/31/03 9:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: same</span><hr size=1> It's probably a hard cap on the maximum amount of mana that goes in the calculation to determine damage.  For instance even if you have say 8000 mana it would only do the random multiplier times the cap (let's say 6000) and if it's 1.5 (around the lowest) it'll do 9000.  They took a completely good skill and beat it into that old moldy nasty ass potato chip that's in every bag. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jago668>jago668</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/31/03 9:38 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: same</span><hr size=1> I heard someone mention it only innate crits anymore because it supposed to be a dot now.  Does the initial damage then hits for 0 damager per tick for a minute.  /shrug, was mentioned shortly after the nerf, when the group of wizards solo'd talendor anyways. <p>Aahzmandius
